    7791             : 
    7792             : /* Support for evaluating a complex relocation.
    7793             : 
    7794             :    Complex relocations are generalized, self-describing relocations.  The
    7795             :    implementation of them consists of two parts: complex symbols, and the
    7796             :    relocations themselves.
    7797             : 
    7798             :    The relocations are use a reserved elf-wide relocation type code (R_RELC
    7799             :    external / BFD_RELOC_RELC internal) and an encoding of relocation field
    7800             :    information (start bit, end bit, word width, etc) into the addend.  This
    7801             :    information is extracted from CGEN-generated operand tables within gas.
    7802             : 
    7803             :    Complex symbols are mangled symbols (BSF_RELC external / STT_RELC
    7804             :    internal) representing prefix-notation expressions, including but not
    7805             :    limited to those sorts of expressions normally encoded as addends in the
    7806             :    addend field.  The symbol mangling format is:
    7807             : 
    7808             :    <node> := <literal>
    7809             :           |  <unary-operator> ':' <node>
    7810             :           |  <binary-operator> ':' <node> ':' <node>
    7811             :           ;
    7812             : 
    7813             :    <literal> := 's' <digits=N> ':' <N character symbol name>
    7814             :              |  'S' <digits=N> ':' <N character section name>
    7815             :              |  '#' <hexdigits>
    7816             :              ;
    7817             : 
    7818             :    <binary-operator> := as in C
    7819             :    <unary-operator> := as in C, plus "0-" for unambiguous negation.  */
    7820             :
